String is a collection of character. 
In java every character is of 16 bits. Hence, Java uses utf-16 encoding for storing the characters.
We can create string in 4 ways.
a. Array/Arraylist of characters
b. String Class 
    Have inbuild functions
    Immutable
    Automatically ThreadSafe
c. StringBuffer Class
    Mutable
    Can be used in a multithreaded environment
d. StringBuilder Class
    Mutable
    Cannot be used only within a thread
    
 Example:
 class Test{
 public static void main(String[] args){
  String str = "geeks";
  System.out.println(str.length());
  System.out.println(str.charAt(3));
  System.out.println(str.substring(2));
  System.out.println(str.substring(2,5));
   // start index is included but not the last index
 }
 }
 Output:
 5
 k
 eks
 eks

Common String Inbuild Functions:
contains(),
equals(),
compareTo(),
indexOf()


